title: Vic Darchinyan vs. Nonito Donaire.avi
description:
In this bout, junior bantamweight contender Nonito Donaire dropped down to 112 pounds to upset previously undefeated IBF flyweight titlist Vic Darchinyan by knocking the power-punching Australian out at 1:38 of the fifth round.

California&#039;s Donaire exhibited superior technique and footwork from the onset of the bout and caught the aggressive lunging champ with a perfect left hook a minute into the fifth round. Australia&#039;s Darchinyan was immediately dropped with the punch, and though he barely made it to his feet before the referee&#039;s "ten count" he stumbled into the ropes where his corner rescued him and the ref wisely waved the contest off.

Donaire improved to 18-1 (11). Darchinyan dropped to 28-1 (22).
